SIMPLE: swifter
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Swifter
<hw>Swift"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Swivel</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A rope used
to retain the bars of the capstan in their sockets while men are turning
it.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A rope used to encircle a boat
longitudinally, to strengthen and defend her sides.</def> <sd>(c)</sd>
<def>The forward shroud of a lower mast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swifter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Swifter
<hw>Swift"er</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>To tighten,
as slack standing rigging, by bringing the opposite shrouds
nearer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swiftfoot</ent>⟦br⟧
